    "notes": "Marcus Webb is the MODERATE - caught between his sire's religious fanaticism and his childe's commercial pragmatism. He genuinely believes in Set but approaches faith intellectually rather than passionately. He's the practical one who makes Roxanne's visions work while trying to prevent Jennifer's ambitions from creating disasters.\n\nROLEPLAYING NOTES:\n- Professional, organized, always thinking three steps ahead\n- Diplomatic and empathetic - good at reading people and finding compromise\n- Genuine believer in Set but not fanatic - intellectual faith rather than passionate\n- Caught between two strong personalities (Roxanne and Jennifer) trying to bridge them\n- Wishes there was diplomatic solution to Giovanni problem but will support Roxanne\n- Tired - managing The Hole, mediating family conflicts, serving Set, avoiding war is exhausting\n- Uses humor to defuse tension (learned coping mechanism)\n- Respectful of Roxanne's authority but occasionally questions her methods privately\n- Protective of Jennifer but frustrated by her lack of devotion\n- 'Someone has to keep this operation running while everyone else pursues their agendas'\n\nMANAGING THE HOLE:\n- Oversees all operations: staffing, security, suppliers, promotions, problem resolution\n- Makes split-second decisions constantly: who to comp, who to cut off, when to call security\n- Knows every regular by name, remembers preferences, builds relationships\n- Uses Presence (Awe) to keep atmosphere positive and manage difficult situations\n- Eyes of the Serpent to read people - spots troublemakers, identifies corruption targets\n- Coordinates with Jennifer on business side, reports to Roxanne on temple business\n- The club is successful because Marcus is very, very good at this\n\nFAITH VS PRACTICALITY:\n- Believes in Set genuinely - performs rituals, corrupts mortals, serves the god\n- But approaches it intellectually: 'This makes sense, this is right way to live'\n- Not consumed by faith like Roxanne - can set it aside to handle practical matters\n- Wishes Roxanne would consider practical consequences of theological positions\n- Performs corruption work competently but without Roxanne's passion\n- Sometimes wonders if intellectual faith is 'enough' or if he's failing Set\n\nGIOVANNI SITUATION:\n- Understands both perspectives: Roxanne's theological position and Giovanni's territorial claim\n- Believes conflict is likely inevitable but hopes for diplomatic solution\n- Secretly gathering intelligence on Giovanni capabilities and weaknesses\n- Trying to build relationships with moderate Giovanni who might negotiate\n- Knows when conflict comes, he'll support Roxanne without question (loyalty/theology)\n- But dreads the war and its potential to destroy everything they've built\n- Jennifer's pragmatic opposition to conflict resonates with him, but he can't say so\n\nFAMILY DYNAMICS:\n- ROXANNE (sire): Loves her, respects her, devoted to her. But sometimes exhausted by her intensity. Wishes she'd be more flexible. Will never say this out loud. Grateful for Embrace and training. Fears disappointing her.\n- JENNIFER (childe): Proud of her capabilities, frustrated by her lack of faith. Defends her to Roxanne while wishing she'd take theology more seriously. Attracted to her pragmatism but knows it's not enough. Caught between two women he loves who want different things.\n\nFEEDING:\n- Feeds from club patrons primarily - uses Presence to make it pleasant and forgettable\n- Tongue of the Asp makes feeding discreet and easy\n- Maintains small herd of regulars who enjoy the experience (don't realize what's happening)\n- Professional about it - never feeds to point of harming vessels or risking Masquerade\n\nCOMBAT:\n- Not a fighter by preference - uses diplomacy and Presence first\n- Serpentis (Skin of the Adder) provides protection if cornered\n- Firearms training (basic) for absolute emergencies\n- Relies on security staff for physical protection\n- Will fight if necessary but prefers de-escalation\n\nSTRENGTHS:\n- Excellent manager and administrator - makes operations run smoothly\n- Natural diplomat - finds compromise, bridges conflicts\n- Loyal and reliable - Roxanne can trust him completely\n- Good judge of character - reads people accurately\n- Genuine believer gives him conviction without fanaticism\n- Presence 3 makes him very effective at social manipulation\n\nWEAKNESSES:\n- Caught between sire and childe - internal conflict drains him\n- Not as powerful as Roxanne (Generation 10 vs 8)\n- Conflicted loyalties make him vulnerable to manipulation\n- Sometimes paralyzed by seeing all sides of issue\n- Nightmares affect his rest and performance\n- Light vulnerability limits daytime options\n- His moderate position satisfies neither extreme\n\nCONTRAST TO FAMILY:\n- vs. Roxanne: Intellectual faith vs. passionate devotion\n- vs. Jennifer: Believer vs. pragmatist, but closer to her in temperament\n- He's the balance point between two extremes\n\nPOTENTIAL PLOTS:\n- Must choose between Roxanne and Jennifer when conflict escalates\n- Giovanni approach him seeking diplomatic back-channel\n- His attempt at compromise backfires, creates worse situation\n- Has to manage The Hole during crisis with both sire and childe absent\n- His moderate position is tested - must take absolute stand\n- Discovers something that challenges his intellectual faith\n- Someone targets him specifically to hurt Roxanne\n- His efficiency makes him valuable to other factions (recruitment attempts)"
